The paper deals with the computation and comparison of error exponents for joint source-channel coding in communication systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Arimoto's algorithm, which is a common tool in source coding (cs.SI) and channel coding (cs.MM). The paper involves the analysis of discrete memoryless systems, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.CC).
